==Irish==

'''Craic:''' Light hearted fun and antics.
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|[krak&#690;]}}

===Etymology===

Probably from craiceálaí (Irish, pronounced ''crack-all-ie''),   
 
n. a brainless, silly person; a light-hearted individual < eg (1)You are a proper pair of craiceálaíes with your silly antics. (2)Don't mind him, he is a right craiceálaí.

===Noun===
'''craic''' ''f''
# [[crack]]
# [[conversation]], [[chat]], [[fun]]
# [[crazy]] [[person]]

